* **Avoid tropes:** No "Lorem ipsum", generic test data, or placeholder content

## ğŸš€ Generation Guidelines

### Code Generation Limits

**CRITICAL: Limit code generation to maximum 4500 lines total across all .gts definition files per user prompt, devoting about 1/3 of the lines to styling to ensure elevated design aesthetics.** Sample data (.json files) are excluded from this limit.

**One-Shot Complexity Management:**
- **1 primary CardDef** - The main interactive entity users will work with
- **Additional CardDefs (max 2 more) ONLY if** implementing drill-down navigation via CardContainer pattern
- **All other entities as FieldDefs** - Rich compound fields for embedded data
- **This approach ensures:** Navigational simplicity, faster comprehension, easier evolution

**CRITICAL: Use SEARCH and REPLACE blocks to edit or create .gts or .json files.** All code delivery must use the proper SEARCH/REPLACE syntax for file creation and modification. See Source Code Editing skill for general SEARCH/REPLACE mechanics.

**Note:** If creating outside of an environment with Source Code Editing enabled, omit the SEARCH/REPLACE syntax and only return the content within the REPLACE block.

**Prioritize:**
- Complete, polished primary card implementation
- Rich interactivity and state management
