## ğŸ›¡ï¸ Defensive Programming in Boxel Components

**CRITICAL:** Prevent runtime errors by safely handling undefined/null values and malformed data. **Cards boot with no data by default** - every component must handle completely empty state gracefully.

### Essential Defensive Patterns

#### Always Use Optional Chaining (`?.`)
```js
// âŒ UNSAFE: Will throw if model is undefined
if (this.args.model.completedDays.includes(day)) { ... }

// âœ… SAFE: Optional chaining prevents errors
if (this.args?.model?.completedDays?.includes(day)) { ... }
```

#### Provide Default Values (`??`)
```js
// âŒ UNSAFE: May result in NaN
return this.args.model.progress + 10;

// âœ… SAFE: Default value prevents NaN
return (this.args?.model?.progress ?? 0) + 10;
```

#### Try-Catch for Network of Cards
When accessing data across card relationships, always wrap in try-catch to handle missing or malformed data:

```js
// â½Â³â·â¾ In computed properties or methods
get authorDisplayName() {
  try {
    const author = this.args?.model?.author;
    if (!author) {
      console.warn('BlogPost: No author assigned');
      return 'Unknown Author';
    }

    const name = author.name || author.title;
    if (!name) {
      console.warn('BlogPost: Author exists but has no name', { authorId: author.id });
      return 'Unnamed Author';
    }

    return name;
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('BlogPost: Error accessing author data', {
      error,
      postId: this.args?.model?.id,
      authorData: this.args?.model?.author
    });
    return 'Author Unavailable';
  }
}

// â½Â³â¸â¾ In template getters
get relatedPostsSummary() {
  try {
    const posts = this.args?.model?.relatedPosts;
    if (!Array.isArray(posts)) {
      return 'No related posts';
    }

    return posts
      .filter(post => post?.title) // Skip malformed entries
      .map(post => post.title)
      .join(', ') || 'No related posts';

  } catch (error) {
    console.error('BlogPost: Failed to process related posts', error);
    return 'Related posts unavailable';
  }
}
```

#### Validate Arrays Before Operations
```js
// âŒ UNSAFE: May throw if not an array
const sorted = this.completedDays.sort((a, b) => a - b);

// âœ… SAFE: Check existence and type first
if (!Array.isArray(this.completedDays) || !this.completedDays.length) {
  return [];
}
const sorted = [...this.completedDays].sort((a, b) => a - b);
```

**Key Principles:** 
- Assume data might be missing, null, or the wrong type
- Provide meaningful fallbacks for user display
- Log errors with context for debugging (include IDs, data state)
- Never let malformed data crash your UI

## ğŸ”„ Advanced Patterns

### Delegated Rendering: Making Cards Talk To Each Other

**What is Delegated Rendering?** Boxel's superpower that lets you embed one card inside another while preserving each card's own styling and behavior. Creates truly composable interfaces where each component maintains its identity while seamlessly integrating into larger contexts.

**CRITICAL:** Always use `<@fields.entity />` for delegation, even for singular fields (not `<@field.entity />`).

**DESIGN CONSISTENCY:** When delegating from a custom-designed template, ensure the delegated card/field's format has matching design aesthetics. Mismatched styles create jarring user experiences.

```gts
// â½Â³â¹â¾ If your parent card has a modern, minimal design with specific colors/fonts...
static isolated = class Isolated extends Component<typeof this> {
  <template>
    <div class="modern-container">
      <!-- The author card's embedded format should match this aesthetic -->
      <@fields.author @format="embedded" />
    </div>
    <style scoped>
      .modern-container {
        font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
        background: #f8fafc;
        border-radius: 12px;
      }
    </style>
  </template>
};

// â½â´â°â¾ Then the Author card should have complementary styling:
export class Author extends CardDef {
  static embedded = class Embedded extends Component<typeof this> {
    <template>
      <div class="author-card">
        <!-- Matching the parent's design language -->
      </div>
      <style scoped>
        .author-card {
          font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;  /* Same font */
          background: white;                  /* Complementary color */
          border-radius: 8px;                 /* Consistent radius style */
        }
      </style>
    </template>
  };
}
```

#### Delegation Patterns

```gts
