### PrerenderedCardSearch: Live Card Displays

Your go-to component for displaying collections of cards with real-time updates. Perfect for dashboards, directories, and live feeds.

**âš ï¸ CRITICAL LIMITATIONS:**
- Returns pre-rendered `card.component` HTML, NOT data objects
- Cannot sort/filter/manipulate results after receiving them
- Cards already include their own styling (fitted/embedded format)
- Parent should only handle layout (grid/list/strip), not card styling

**Common Mistake - This WON'T work:**
```gts
// âŒ WRONG - Can't sort rendered components
<:response as |cards|>
  {{#each (this.sortCards cards) as |card|}}
    <card.component />
  {{/each}}
</:response>
```

**Correct Pattern with CardContainer:**
```gts
{{#let (component @context.prerenderedCardSearchComponent) as |PrerenderedCardSearch|}}
  <PrerenderedCardSearch
    @query={{this.query}}
    @format="embedded"
    @realms={{this.realms}}
    @isLive={{true}}
  >
    <:loading>
      <div class="loading-state">Loading cards...</div>
    </:loading>

    <:response as |cards|>
      {{#if (gt cards.length 0)}}
        <ul class="card-list">
          {{#each cards key="url" as |card|}}
            <li class="card-item">
              <CardContainer
                {{@context.cardComponentModifier
                  cardId=card.url
                  format='data'
                  fieldType=undefined
                  fieldName=undefined
                }}
                @displayBoundaries={{true}}
              >
                <card.component />
              </CardContainer>
            </li>
          {{/each}}
        </ul>
      {{else}}
        <div class="empty-state">No cards found</div>
      {{/if}}
    </:response>
  </PrerenderedCardSearch>
{{/let}}

<style scoped>
  /* Only handle layout - cards style themselves */
  .card-list {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  /* Don't add borders/shadows - CardContainer handles chrome */
  .card-item {
    /* Layout only */
  }
</style>
```

**Sorting/Filtering Options:**

1. **Use Query Filters (Recommended):**
```gts
get query(): Query {
  return {
    filter: {
      on: {
        module: 'https://my.realm/product',
        name: 'Product'
      },
      eq: {
        category: 'electronics'
      },
      gt: {
        price: 100
      }
    },
    sort: [{
      by: 'price',
      direction: 'asc'
    }]
  };
}
```

2. **Use getCards API for Data Manipulation:**
```gts
import { getCards } from '@cardstack/runtime-common';

// When you need to sort/filter after retrieval
async loadAndSortCards() {
  const cards = await getCards(this.query, this.realms);
  this.sortedCards = cards.sort((a, b) => b.rating - a.rating);
  // Now render manually, not with PrerenderedCardSearch
}
```

**Best Practices:**
- Let cards handle their own internal styling
- Use query filters for sorting/filtering when possible
- Only use getCards when you need complex data manipulation
- Keep container styling minimal (spacing, layout only)

