**Relationship Path Tracking:** When creating related JSON instances, maintain a mental map of your file paths. Links between instances must use the exact relative paths you've created - consistency prevents broken relationships.

## ğŸ“Š JSON Instance Format Quick Reference

**When creating `.json` card instances via SEARCH/REPLACE, follow this structure:**

**Naming:** Use natural names for JSON files (e.g., `Author/jane-doe.json`, `Product/laptop-pro.json`) - don't append `-sample-data`

**Path Consistency:** When creating multiple related JSON instances, track the exact file paths you create. Relationship links must match these paths exactly - if you create `Author/dr-nakamura.json`, reference it as `"../Author/dr-nakamura"` from other instances.

### Root Structure
All data wrapped in a `data` object with:
* `type`: Always `"card"` for instances
* `attributes`: Field values go here
* `relationships`: Links to other cards
* `meta.adoptsFrom`: Connection to GTS definition

### Instance Template
```json
{
  "data": {
    "type": "card",
    "attributes": {
      // Field values here
    },
    "relationships": {
      // Card links here
    },
    "meta": {
      "adoptsFrom": {
        "module": "../path-to-gts-file",
        "name": "CardDefClassName"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

### Field Value Patterns

**Simple fields** (`contains(StringField)`, etc.):
```json
"attributes": {
  "title": "My Title",
  "price": 29.99,
  "isActive": true
}
```

**Compound fields** (`contains(AddressField)` - a FieldDef):
```json
"attributes": {
  "address": {
    "street": "4827 Riverside Terrace",
    "city": "Portland",
    "postalCode": "97205"
  }
}
```

**Array fields** (`containsMany`):
```json
"attributes": {
  "tags": ["urgent", "review", "frontend"],
  "phoneNumbers": [
    { "number": "+1-503-555-0134", "type": "work" },
    { "number": "+1-971-555-0198", "type": "mobile" }
  ]
}
```

### Relationship Patterns

**Single link** (`linksTo`):
```json
"relationships": {
  "author": {
    "links": {
      "self": "../Author/dr-nakamura"
    }
  }
}
```

**Multiple links** (`linksToMany`) - note the `.0`, `.1` pattern:
```json
"relationships": {
  "teamMembers.0": {
    "links": { "self": "../Person/kai-nakamura" }
  },
  "teamMembers.1": {
    "links": { "self": "../Person/esperanza-cruz" }
  }
}
```

**Empty linksToMany** - when no relationships exist:
```json
"relationships": {
  "nextLevels": {
    "links": {
      "self": null
    }
  }
}
```
Note: Use `null`, not an empty array `[]`

### Path Conventions
* **Module paths**: Relative to JSON location, no `.gts` extension
  * Local: `"../author"` or `"../../shared/address-field"`
  * Base: `"https://cardstack.com/base/string"`
* **Relationship paths**: Relative paths, no `.json` extension
  * `"../Author/jane-doe"` not `"../Author/jane-doe.json"`
* **Date formats**: 
  * DateField: `"2024-11-15"`
  * DatetimeField: `"2024-11-15T10:00:00Z"`

## ğŸš« Common Mistakes to Avoid

### 1. Using contains/containsMany with CardDef
```gts
// âŒ WRONG
export class Auction extends CardDef {
  @field auctionItems = containsMany(AuctionItem); // AuctionItem is a CardDef
}

// âœ… CORRECT
export class Auction extends CardDef {
  @field auctionItems = linksToMany(AuctionItem); // Use linksToMany for CardDef
}
```

### 2. Template Calculation Mistakes
```gts
// âŒ WRONG - JavaScript/constructors in template
<span>Total: {{@model.price * @model.quantity}}</span>
<span>{{if @model.currentMonth @model.currentMonth (formatDateTime (new Date()) "MMMM YYYY")}}</span>

// âœ… CORRECT - Use helpers or computed property
<span>Total: {{multiply @model.price @model.quantity}}</span>
<span>{{if @model.currentMonth @model.currentMonth this.currentMonthDisplay}}</span>
```

### 3. Using Reserved Words as Field Names
```gts
// âŒ WRONG - JavaScript reserved words will break compilation
export class DataModel extends CardDef {
  @field type = contains(StringField);     // 'type' is reserved
  @field class = contains(StringField);    // 'class' is reserved
}

// âŒ WRONG - Defining same field twice in your own class
export class Person extends CardDef {
  @field name = contains(StringField);
  @field name = contains(StringField, { computeVia: ... }); // ERROR! Duplicate
}

// âœ… CORRECT - Use descriptive alternatives
export class DataModel extends CardDef {
  @field recordType = contains(StringField);  // Instead of 'type'
  @field category = contains(StringField);    // Instead of 'class'
}

// âœ… CORRECT - Override inherited fields with computed versions
export class Person extends CardDef {
  @field fullName = contains(StringField);

  // OK to override parent's title
  @field title = contains(StringField, {
    computeVia: function() { return this.fullName ?? 'Unnamed'; }
  });
}
```

### 4. Missing Exports
```gts
// âŒ WRONG - Missing export will break module loading
class BlogPost extends CardDef { // Missing 'export'
}

// âŒ WRONG - Separate export statement
class BlogPost extends CardDef { }
export { BlogPost };

// âœ… CORRECT - Always export CardDef and FieldDef classes inline
export class BlogPost extends CardDef {
}
```

### 5. Missing Spacing for Auto-Collections
```gts
// âŒ WRONG - No spacing wrapper for delegated items
<@fields.items @format="embedded" />

// âŒ WRONG - Container styling won't reach containsMany items
<div class="items-container">
  <@fields.items @format="embedded" />
</div>

<style scoped>
.items-container {
  display: flex;
  gap: 0.75rem; /* Won't work! */
}
</style>

// âœ… CORRECT - Target .containsMany-field
<div class="items-container">
  <@fields.items @format="embedded" />
</div>

<style scoped>
.items-container > .containsMany-field {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 0.75rem; /* REQUIRED: Adds spacing between items */
}
</style>
```

### 6. Using Emoji or Boxel Icons in Templates
```hbs
<!-- âŒ WRONG - Emoji varies by OS/platform -->
<h4>ğŸ¯ Daily Goals</h4>
<button>ğŸ’¬ Comments</button>

<!-- âŒ WRONG - Can't be sure Boxel icons exist -->
<h4><TargetIcon class="icon" /> Daily Goals</h4>
<button><MessageCircleIcon class="icon" /> Comments</button>

<!-- âœ… CORRECT - Use inline SVG in templates -->
<h4>
  <svg class="icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
    <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/>
    <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="6"/>
    <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="2"/>
  </svg>
  Daily Goals
</h4>
<button>
  <svg class="icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
    <path d="M21 15a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H7l-4 4V5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h14a2 2 0 0 1 2 2z"/>
  </svg>
  Comments
