  <rect x="10" y="10" width="80" height="80" />
</svg>
<style scoped>
  .gradient-svg rect {
    fill: #6366f1; /* Fallback solid color */
  }
  /* Apply gradient as background to the SVG element itself */
  .gradient-svg {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #6366f1, #8b5cf6);
    border-radius: 8px;
  }
</style>
```

**Rule:** Avoid `url(#id)` references in SVGs (for gradients, patterns, clips, etc.) as Boxel cannot route these correctly. Instead, use CSS alternatives to style SVG elements when available. For gradients specifically, use CSS `linear-gradient()` or `radial-gradient()` on SVG elements rather than SVG `<linearGradient>` or `<radialGradient>`.

